==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Studding sail
<hw>Stud"ding sail`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A light
sail set at the side of a principal or square sail of a vessel in free
winds, to increase her speed. Its head is bent to a small spar which is
called the <xex>studding-sail boom</xex>. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of
<er>Sail</er>.</def> <rj><au>Toten.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Student</ent>⟦br⟧
